To find the principal \(P\) when simple interest \(I\), rate \(r\), and time \(t\) are known, use  
 \(I = Prt\).  

Here \(I = \$495\), \(r = 6\% = 0.06\), and \(t = 3\) years.  Solve for \(P\):  
\[
P = \frac{I}{r\,t}
  = \frac{495}{0.06 \times 3}
  = \frac{495}{0.18}
  = 2750.
\]

Answer: \(\$2{,}750\).
